Lord Stewart of Dirleton QC, the Advocate General for Scotland, said the move is "premature" and the First Minister did “not have the necessary degree of confidence”. A decision from the court on whether to accept the proposal for an independence referendum on October 19 next year, is expected in the autumn. The Government says "now is not the time" for another referendum amid the cost of living crisis and the ongoing war in Ukraine. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 